===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} ''[[mortier]]'', from {{etyl|la}} ''[[mortarium]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|ɔː(r)tə(r)}}
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈmɔːtɘ(ɹ)/}} {{X-SAMPA|/"mO:t@(r)/}}
* {{audio|En-us-mortar.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{uncountable}} A mixture of [[lime]] or [[cement]], [[sand]] and [[water]] used for [[bonding]] [[brick]]s and [[stone]]s.
# {{countable|military}} A muzzle-loading, [[indirect]] fire [[weapon]] with a tube length of 10 to 20 [[caliber]]s.
# {{countable}} A hollow [[vessel]] used to [[pound]], [[crush]], [[rub]], [[grind]] or [[mix]] [[ingredient]]s with a [[pestle]].

